HEADWORD: Integrator
<hw>In"te*gra`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Math. &
Mech.)</fld> <def>That which integrates; esp., an instrument by means of
which the area of a figure can be measured directly, or its moment of
inertia, or statical moment, etc., be determined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Integrity</ent>⟦br⟧
